        <p>I enjoy the simple things in life. The power of a good laugh, jamming out to an old mixed-tape, seeing other people happy...
          I very much enjoy helping others. I worked as a Neuro ICU nurse for about 2-3 years and then switched to pediatrics for another 2 years.
          I really enjoyed both fields, but found I couldn't stop bringing the work home with me. I then realized I could help people in other ways
          and after doing some soul-searching, re-evaluating my interests, and reviewing what qualities I'm strong at, programming seemed to fit
          the bill. It also helped that my fiance is a programmer and could give me some great insight into the career. My interest in the career
          grew rapidly! I love to see what I can accomplish and what I can build. It's amazing to see some of the things you can do with programming.</p>

        <p>Aside from career choices, I moved to Denver Colorado from Phoenix Arizona towards the end of 2012. I had lived in Arizona for the previous
